>
<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Value_with_unit_arm
   <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm">
</ext_description>


  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.length_measure">
A <b>length_measure</b> is  a number that represents  a length quantity.
</ext_description>
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.plane_angle_measure">
A <b>plane_angle_measure</b> is  a number that represents  a plane angle quantity.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Type: number_value 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.any_number_value">
	A <b>any_number_value</b> is a value that is a number and that is not specific of a particular kind of quantity.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Type: string_value 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.any_string_value">
	A <b>any_string_value</b> is a value that is a string and that is not specific of a particular kind of quantity.. 
</ext_description>


<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Amount_of_substance_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Amount_of_substance_unit">
An <b>Amount_of_substance_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 in which the number of elementary entities of
a substance as compared to the number of atoms in 0.012 kilograms of carbon-12 is expressed.
<note number="1">This definition applies to the SI quantity 'mole'. When the mole is used, the elementary entities, whose
quantity is expressed, must be specified . They may be atoms, molecules, ions, electrons or other particles or
specified groups of such particles (see ISO 31-8).
</note>
<note number="2">This unit corresponds to one of the seven fundamental quantities as specified in ISO 1000.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Context_dependent_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Context_dependent_unit">
A <b>Context_dependent_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 that is not related to the system of units defined in this part of ISO 10303.
<example>The number of parts in an assembly is a physical quantity that may be measured in a unit called
'parts'. Such a unit cannot be related to an SI unit.</example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Context_dependent_unit.wr:WR1">
The <b>Context_dependent_unit</b> shall have a name.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Conversion_based_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Conversion_based_unit">
A <b>Conversion_based_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 that that is based on another and related by a conversion factor.
<note>A <b>Conversion_based_unit</b> is often used to convert a unit in one system of units to a similar unit in another system.</note> 
<example>An Imperial inch is 25.4 millimetres</example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Conversion_based_unit.wr:WR1">
The <b>Conversion_based_unit</b> shall have a name.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Conversion_based_unit  Attribute: conversion_factor 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Conversion_based_unit.conversion_factor">
the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit"/>

 that defines the conversion.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Derived_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit">
A <b>Derived_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 that is defined by an expression of other units. 
<example>Newtons per square metre is a derived unit.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Derived_unit  Attribute: elements 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit.elements">
  <p>
a set of units and their exponents whose product defines the
<b>Derived_unit</b>.
</p>
<note>Each element is one term in the <b>Derived_unit</b>.</note></ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Derived_unit_element  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit_element">
A <b>Derived_unit_element</b> is the association of an exponent with a <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Derived_unit_element  Attribute: base_unit 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit_element.base_unit">
the unit of a term in the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Derived_unit_element  Attribute: exponent 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit_element.exponent">
the real number for the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Derived_unit"/>.</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Duration 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Duration">
A <b>Duration</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit"/>

 that defines the magnitude of a time interval.
      </ext_description>
			
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Duration.wr:WR1">
the unit of the <b>Duration</b> shall be a <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Time_unit"/>.
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Electric_current_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Electric_current_unit">
An <b>Electric_current_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 with which movement of electrically charged particles is expressed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Length_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Length_unit">
	A <b>Length_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 in which distances are expressed. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Luminous_intensity_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Luminous_intensity_unit">
A <b>Luminous_intensity_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 in which the brightness of a body is expressed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Mass_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Mass_unit">
A <b>Mass_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 with which mass is expressed.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Plane_angle_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Plane_angle_unit">
	A <b>Plane_angle_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 by which a angles in planes are expressed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Ratio_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Ratio_unit">
A <b>Ratio_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

that expresses the dimensionless ratio of two quantities of the same kind. 
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Solid_angle_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Solid_angle_unit">
A <b>Solid_angle_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 that is solid angle.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Thermodynamic_temperature_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Thermodynamic_temperature_unit">
A <b>Thermodynamic_temperature_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 in which the degree of heat of a body is expressed.</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Time_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Time_unit">
A <b>Time_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 with which the duration of a period is expressed.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Uncertainty_with_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Uncertainty_with_unit">
An <b>Uncertainty_with_unit</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit"/>

 that specifies the uncertainty that
applies to a type of measure. An <b>Uncertainty_with_unit</b> applies to each <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.Representation_item"/>

that uses the type of measure specified in the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit.value_component"/>

 of the <b>Uncertainty_with_unit</b>.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Uncertainty_with_unit.name">
the words by which the <b>Uncertainty_with_unit</b> is known.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Uncertainty_with_unit.description">the 
text that provides further information about the <b>Uncertainty_with_unit</b>. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Unit">
A <b>Unit</b> is a unit quantity.
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Unit.name">
the words by which the <b>Unit</b> is known. 
</ext_description>

  <ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Unit.si_unit">
the boolean value that indicates whether the <b>Unit</b> is one of the units defined in the SI system.
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Value_with_unit  
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit">
A <b>Value_with_unit</b> is the specification of a physical quantity by its value and its unit.
      </ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Value_with_unit  Attribute: unit 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit.unit">
the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Unit"/>

 with which the physical quantity is expressed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Value_with_unit_arm  Entity: Value_with_unit  Attribute: value_component 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit.value_component">
the value of the quantity.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>

